  "original_title": "\u0ba8\u0b9f\u0bc1\u0b95\u0bcd\u0b95\u0b9f\u0bb2\u0bbf\u0bb2\u0bcd \u0ba4\u0ba4\u0bcd\u0ba4\u0bb3\u0bbf\u0ba4\u0bcd\u0ba4 55 \u0baa\u0bc7\u0bb0\u0bcd \u0bae\u0bc0\u0b9f\u0bcd\u0baa\u0bc1",
  "text_idx": {
    "en": {
      "title": "Rescue of 55 people stranded in the middle of the sea",
      "author": "unknown",
      "body_lines": [
        "The Sri Lankan Navy has rescued 55 people aboard a fishing trawler that got stuck in strong winds about 390 nautical miles south-east of Ambandottai while trying to go abroad illegally.",
        "They were rescued yesterday (12) by the Sri Lankan Navy's Maritime Search and Rescue Coordination Center when the boat was in distress.",
        "The Navy has announced that 55 people, including 46 men, 3 women and 6 children, were traveling on the said boat, including 5 people who assisted in the illegal journey.",
        "The Navy mentioned that the boat they were traveling in was damaged due to strong winds and could not be brought ashore due to sea water ingress.",
        "People from Trincomalee, Mannar, Vavuniya, Kilinochchi, Mullaitivu, Jaffna and Puttalam have been rescued by the Navy. (a)"
      ],
